def predict(x, F, P, Q, z, R):
    xp = F @ x
    y = z - xp
    S = Q + R
    K = np.exp(-0.1 * P) @ y
    x = xp + K
    return xp, P, y, S, K, x
```

### Implementation 7: Adaptive Kalman Filter with Online Tuning
```python
def predict(x, F, P, Q, z, R):
    xp = F @ x
    y = z - xp
    S = Q + R
    K = np.zeros_like(P)
    for i in range(len(x)):
        K[i, i] = 0.3 * (1 + np.mean(y[:i]))
    x = xp + K @ y
    return xp, P, y, S, K, x
```

